---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Matteo Curcio" path="/about">
  <p class="kicker">About</p>
  <h1>Post-production with taste, restraint, and repeatable process.</h1>

  <div class="two-col section">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I work across color, editing, and motion, with an emphasis on systems that stay stable under deadlines:
        clean handoffs, consistent versions, and a clear story for every deliverable.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is intentionally lightweight. It’s designed so the work loads instantly and the pages are easy to
        maintain without a plugin stack.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you want, send a brief and I’ll reply with a suggested workflow: what to lock, what to iterate, and what to
        deliver.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="panel">
      <p class="kicker">Links</p>
      <p class="post-meta">
        Behance, Instagram, YouTube, and more live on the current homepage footer. I can also surface them here as a
        dedicated “Links” section.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

